entries.meaning: A group of nine, particularly (music) a tuplet of nine notes.
examples: Coordinate terms: singlet, couplet, triplet, quadruplet, tetraplet, pentuplet, sextuplet, septuplet, octuplet, decuplet, centuplet, multiplet

entries.meaning: One of a group of nine, particularly one of nine babies born from the same mother at one time.
